CHAPTER 3 â€“ SharePoint Online Architecture (Complete Breakdown)

SharePoint Online is built on Multi-tenant cloud architecture.

Layers of Architecture:

1. Tenant Level

Your Microsoft 365 subscription

Contains all SharePoint sites

Managed by Global Admin & SharePoint Admin



2. Site Collections (Sites)

Every team site/communication site is a site collection.

Root site (https://tenant.sharepoint.com/)



3. Sites & Subsites

Modern approach: avoid subsites, use independent sites connected via Hub sites.



4. Lists & Libraries

Stores structured information

Document libraries: files

Lists: data tables (similar to Excel)



5. Pages

Content pages built with web parts



6. Web Parts

UI building blocks: Hero, List, Document Library, Embed, Image, etc.



7. Storage

Comes from OneDrive + SharePoint pooled storage

Auto-expanding storage in Microsoft 365 plans





