ğŸ§© CHAPTER 29 â€“ What is SPFx?

The SharePoint Framework (SPFx) is a client-side development model used to build:

âœ” Web Parts
âœ” Extensions
âœ” Custom Forms
âœ” Command Sets
âœ” Application Customizers
âœ” Full React apps in SharePoint

Key Features

100% client-side

Runs in modern SharePoint pages

Supports React, Angular, Vue, jQuery, plain JS

Uses TypeScript + Node.js + Webpack

Integrates with Microsoft Graph

Supports Teams apps

Works with On-Prem (SP 2016, 2019) and Online



---

ğŸ§© CHAPTER 30 â€“ SPFx Architecture

SPFx runs directly in the browser.
It is built using:

Node.js â€“ runtime

Yeoman â€“ scaffolding

Gulp â€“ task runner

Webpack â€“ bundling

TypeScript â€“ scripting

React â€“ UI framework (recommended)


Architecture Layers

+-------------------------------+
|      SharePoint Page         |
+-------------------------------+
|     SPFx Framework APIs      |
+-------------------------------+
|     Your Web Part Code       |
+-------------------------------+
|     TypeScript + React       |
+-------------------------------+
| Node.js + Gulp + Webpack     |
+-------------------------------+

SPFx renders components inside a SharePoint Canvas.


---

ğŸ§© CHAPTER 31 â€“ Environment Setup

Install the necessary tools:

âœ” 1. Install Node.js

Supported versions change oftenâ€”use Microsoft recommended LTS.

https://nodejs.org/

âœ” 2. Install Yeoman & SPFx Generator

npm install -g yo gulp
npm install -g @microsoft/generator-sharepoint

âœ” 3. Install Visual Studio Code

IDE for SPFx.

âœ” 4. Install Git

For version control.

âœ” 5. Install PnPjs Library (optional but recommended)

npm install @pnp/sp @pnp/graph


---

ğŸ§© CHAPTER 32 â€“ Create Your First SPFx Web Part

