8.11 Permissions & Access Management (MOST IMPORTANT)

Default Permission Levels:

Permission	Description

Full Control	Admin
Edit	Add/edit/delete items
Contribute	Add/edit items
Read	View only
Limited Access	Required for hierarchy


Permission Hierarchy:

1. Site Collection Admin


2. Site Owner


3. Members (Edit)


4. Visitors (Read)



SharePoint Groups:

Owners

Members

Visitors

Custom groups


Permission Best Practices:

âœ” Use groups, not individuals
âœ” Break inheritance only when needed
âœ” Avoid giving Edit to everyone
âœ” Use â€œAccess Requestâ€ feature
âœ” Use â€œShareâ€ carefully
âœ” Apply labels or DLP for confidential docs


